BIG PROJECT REVEAL! ✨ Happy Friday friends! I’m SO excited to share that our @LakeTahoeCabin remodel is finally done ✔️🙌🏼

This was our first remodel and we had no idea what we were getting into! We took this 1970s cabin down to the studs, moved structural walls and completely reimagined the entire interior with high end furnishings, appliances and decor👌🏼

It took 2 years to complete 😱 we argued about every single detail and hubby and I almost got divorced (like 10 times!) but I’m so proud to say it turned out even better than I ever imagined (which is shocking considering we had no clue what we were doing)! 😅

We will be opening rental bookings in a few weeks but in the meantime if you’d like to stay here email me vanessamrivers@gmail.com and I’ll set you up! 😁 We just finished the house so it is open through NYE if you’re looking for a last minute holiday getaway rental!🎄☃️ 

A little about our @LakeTahoeCabin : Located in Carnelian Bay, one of the most sought after areas on the North Shore, this completely remodeled 4 bedroom, 5 bath home, including a separate bunk house with a kitchenette + a loft, boasts sweeping views of Lake Tahoe amidst a quiet forest setting. Just minutes from the lake, only 12 miles to Palisades Tahoe Resort and 13 miles to Northstar Resort 🏂⛷ this modern cabin is ideally situated to enjoy the best of Lake Tahoe year round! 👌🏼

In the main house there are two master bedrooms, both with walk in closets, ensuite bathrooms and incredible lake views. The third bedroom also offers sparkling lake views, an en suite bathroom with a double vanity, and a new gas burning fireplace. This beautiful home boasts three decks, three fireplaces and plenty of ski equipment storage. You’ll surely fall in love with the upscale mountain modern feel and the great energy this cabin exudes!🌲🏔✨

I call this series Bad Parenting 101…

Sadie: “Why does the snowman have boobs?” ⛄️
Me: “Because she’s a mom.”

The rest is self-explanatory 🥂😅

8 years ago today! 💍💒🥰

On December 29th, 2014 we eloped to Barbados and said “I do” with our toes in the sand. It was just us and it was magical ✨ 

Studies suggest that most marriages that fail will do so within the first 2 years. Another difficult period often happens within the 5-8 year mark so I guess we are just getting over the second hump? 🤔😅

I don’t post many photos of my husband Steve because he likes his privacy and despises social media 😅 but today I wanted to share these photos and say that I’m so grateful I get to be with such a kind, smart, generous, patient, fun, loving man 🥰🙏🏼

But no one is perfect. Marriage is tough. Steve and I have A LOT of problems we are constantly trying to work through but after over 11 years together and 8 years of marriage we genuinely love and LIKE each other and enjoy each others company 😍😍

And to be totally honest out of the two of us, Steve is the better spouse by far…. Steve has always supported me in my dreams and he let’s me be me. He has never tried to change me - I’m NOT a morning person, I’m impatient, I can be selfish, I’m a horrible cook, I have a wild streak and a temper (I blame my Italian heritage😅🇮🇹), I need my alone time and my girl time, and I constantly have to be working on something new and creative and he just lets me be and loves me (in spite of my pain in the a$$ self)! 🥰 

If you’re reading this and still looking for “the one” I want to say to you don’t settle. Your person is out there for you, the timing might not be what you want but keep an open mind and heart and the right person will come along ❤️🙏🏼

Happy 2023 friends! 🥳 

Took the first 4 days of the year off from social media to set intentions for the new year - excited - it’s going to be a good one full of lots of adventures! ✈️ 

What destination is at the top of your 2023 bucketlist? 🌎

This image has me dreaming of going back to Canada 🇨🇦 One of the most iconic images of the Canadian Rockies has become this shot of Moraine Lake in Banff National Park 🌲This alpine lake is fed by a glacier and is an otherworldly turquoise blue 💙 

I first visited Canada on a girls getaway in 2015 and fell in love with the cute little town of Banff and the awe inspiring topography of Moraine Lake and Lake Louise 🥰🙌🏼

Of course these lakes have become a very popular attraction in recent years but if you haven’t been I highly suggest putting the providence of Alberta on your 2023 bucketlist 🌎 Canada is arguably one of the most beautifully rugged countries in the world! 🇨🇦🫶🏼

Tips For Visiting Moraine Lake 🏔🛶🌲🇨🇦

• The road to Moraine Lake reopens June 2023
• The lake is frozen October to late May so plan your visit from June - Sept 
• Sept is an ideal time to visit if you want to miss the high season summer crowds 
• There are several great walks / hikes around the lake 
• The most famous is this short walk up to Rockpile Trail where I took this photo 
• But the father you hike the less tourists there will be and the better views and photos you’ll get! 

If you have questions about visiting Moraine Lake leave these in the comments 👇🏼 Also please let us know - what destination is at the top of your 2023 bucketlist?! 🌎

It’s dumping in Tahoe! ❄️ Who’s ready for an epic ski season 🙋🏼‍♀️ @LakeTahoeCabin 

We’re heading up to Tahoe the first weekend of Feb 🎿🏔 If you’re going to be there message me so we can meet up and ski together! 🏂⛷🥰

One of my 2023 goals is to start jumping again! 🏂 

Most people don’t know this about me but I used to work as a ski & snowboard instructor - I lived in Lake Tahoe for a season and I taught at the ski school at Northstar ⛷ I also lived in Big Bear for the 2007 / 2008 ski season and taught private snowboard lessons at Big Bear Resort 🏂

During my time in Big Bear I lived at a hotel that used to be called “The Block” owned by pro snowboarder Marc Frank Montoya, and I was one of the cast members in Marc’s reality TV show about snowboarders 🎥🏂 The show was a total flop but the experience was so much fun 🤩

I was 25 and I got to spend the season boarding with pro snowboarders like @ShaunWhite and Tara Dakides and I got got pretty good at jumping that winter and doing boxes and rails (watch to the end of the reel to see a couple photos from the show)… but fast forward 15 years, I now snowboard like an old lady 👵🏻😂

But this year I’ve decided I’m going to try to get back into it and start jumping again - purely for the fun of it 🏔🏂🥰 It seems scary (and it kind of is) but it’s such an incredible rush when you’re in the air - it feels like flying and it’s so addicting!

I know most people have serious resolutions and this seems silly in comparison but one thing I’ve realized recently is the older you get the quicker life goes 💨 I want to work hard but I also want to make sure I keep having FUN - otherwise what’s the point of it all?! 🏂🤩🥳

Take me to the sea, where my heart will always be 🌊 

One of my other 2023 goals is to start shortboarding again! 🏄🏼‍♀️😁

I’ve been pretty lazy with my surfing the last few years... I pulled out my old 8ft board and have been riding that most of the time because it’s so easy to catch waves with a big board. I also recently bought a 7’6” fun shaped board that I tried out the other day. It’s really fun but it reminded me how much I miss shortboarding 🏄🏼‍♀️ 

I have 5 beautiful shortboards in my garage collecting dust that I’m going to break out again this year and get back into it. I have to remind myself I’m turning 40 this month, not 80 🏄🏼‍♀️😅 

Although when I’m 80 I still plan to be surfing! 🌊👊🏼

Throw back to surfing @Nihi 🌊🏄🏼‍♀️

As a surfer, this is hands down my favorite luxury hotel in the world! 🙌🏼 If you surf (or love remote destinations) you have to splurge on a stay at Nihi 🌊🌴

It’s a bit of a trek to get to this incredible resort on Sumba Island (in Eastern Indonesia) but that’s part of the charm and the journey is well worth it! ✈️🌍 

Nihi has their own private surf break and the property is absolutely incredible in every way ✨👌🏼 

I stayed here on a press trip in 2016 and I’ve been dreaming of going back ever since 💭 🌊🏄🏼‍♀️🤞🏼

Last day of my 30s 😅🥳

Seriously can’t believe I’m turning 40 tomorrow! 🙈 The last time I checked I was in my twenties! I’ve definitely been having a bit of a mid life crisis the past year feeling like there’s so much I haven’t accomplished that I wanted to by this point… 

Sadie has definitely picked up on this and was especially happy to relish in my big 4-O B-Day anxiety this morning at breakfast while she danced around the kitchen and sang “Mamas last day of being 39!!!” 🎶🤣 

But I have to say the biggest blessing of getting older is that you really appreciate what’s important in life - FAMILY ❤️ Despite anything I don’t have, of haven’t accomplished my cup is overflowing because of my family - I’m so incredibly lucky and grateful to have my beautiful daughter and my loving husband 🥰🙏🏼 

But now for a dose of reality - my family life growing up was definitely not like these Instagram photos. It was beautiful and magical but also crazy, chaotic and wild roller coaster of traumatic and unbelievable experiences. I don’t have a publication date yet but I wrote an entire book about it that I can’t wait to share with you! 📚 

I just mention this because I don’t want you to look at my photos and think I have this perfect family life. No one’s life or family is perfect BUT friends and family, the people who really love you, make life worth living 🙏🏼❤️ 

So today on my last day of being 39 I’m most grateful for my family and all the adventures we’ve had together. Sharing a few of my favorites: 

Photo 1: Oahu 🇺🇸 
Photo 2: England 🏴󠁧󠁢󠁥󠁮󠁧󠁿 
Photo 3: Jamaica 🇯🇲 
Photo 4: Mykonos 🇬🇷 
Photo 5: Bainbridge Island 🇺🇸
Photo 6: Paris 🇫🇷 
Photo 7: London 🇬🇧 
Photo 8: Mexico 🇲🇽 
Photo 9: Malibu 🇺🇸
Photo 10: Aspen 🇺🇸

Cheers to another 40+ years of adventures! ✈️ 🌎

This is 29 + 11 ✌🏼🥳

Age is just an addition problem right? 😅 I’m pretty bad at math… Clearly I’m not growing up anytime soon 🤔 

Like my favorite quote says “You can only be young once. But you can be immature forever.” Here’s to 40+ more years of immaturity 😁

Don’t quit your daydream ✨ @LakeTahoeCabin 

So, so excited! Heading up to Lake Tahoe today to stay at our cabin for the FIRST TIME since its been done being remodeled! 🙌🏼 Ever since I was in college I dreamed of having a house in Tahoe! It took me almost 20 years to make that dream a reality and I’m so glad I never gave up on it. If you’re reading this, this is YOUR SIGN to never give up on your dreams ✨ 

It took us over 2 years to remodel this 1970s cabin - we honestly didn’t know what we wete getting into - it was a way bigger project than we expected BUT it turned out better than I imagined which is shocking since we had no clue what we were doing! 😅

Here’s a peak inside the cabin and detached bunk house. All the bedrooms have en suite bathrooms and sweeping lake views ✨ 🥰

If you like what you see and you’re interested in RENTING our @LakeTahoeCabin for an upcoming Tahoe trip reach out to me! 🏡 ⛷️🛶 💙

Hello from Tahoe 👋🏼🏂 @LakeTahoeCabin 

Thank you to everyone who sent me messages checking to make sure we made it to Tahoe 🥰 We are here safe but poor Sadie has been very sick and hasn’t been able to ski 😞

It’s dumping in Tahoe today and we are snowed in so I’m sharing a few photos from our day skiing yesterday at @northstar_california 🏂⛷️ 

Steve and I got to ski half day while Sadie stayed home with a babysitter to rest 😴 I feel so bad, she often gets sick before or on our trips and misses out. Traveling with young kids can be tough but it’s worth it for the times they do get to enjoy the adventure 🌎✈️ 

Hoping Sadie feels better tomorrow so we can at least build a snowman together before we head home ⛄️🤞🏼

Epic powder day at @northstar_california with @broker_yulia ⛷️🏂❄️☀️🥰🥂 

There’s so much snow in Lake Tahoe right now ❄️🙌🏼 If you’re looking for a place to rent for a ski trip check out our 👉🏼 @LakeTahoeCabin and message me if you’d like to book it 💙 Our Cabin is just 12 miles to Palisades Tahoe Resort and 13 miles to Northstar 🏔️

See you on the slopes! ⛄️

When life gives you snow… make snow angels ❄️😇 @LakeTahoeCabin 

Sadie’s Winter Tips: “Open your mouth when it’s snowing and don’t eat yellow snow!” ⛄️

Thank God I have her around to babysit me 😅

social_posts.post_text: It’s ski week for Los Angeles schools - everyone is headed to ski… so we’re headed to Baja 😁🇲🇽🌮🍹☀️🌊🏄‍♀️

Instagram v. Reality 🤔

INSTAGRAM: Seemingly carefree vacay enjoying cocktails at @oneandonlypalmilla with two of me fave ladies @larabrody and @broker_yulia 🍹🇲🇽 

REALITY: Sadie and I were wsick the entire time we were in Mex 🤦🏼‍♀️ I was washing down multiple Sudafed a day with margaritas hoping the combination would allow me to somehow enjoy our trip still. It sort of worked for the first two days but then Sadie’s cold turned into pneumonia 😭 We basically didn’t sleep for 3 nights straight since she was up all night coughing. We ended up flying home early, arriving in LA to unusually cold weather and pouring rain 🌧️ 

We took Sadie straight to urgent care in Santa Monica and then had to go to two other urgent cares over the next 24 hours to find one that could do a chest X-Ray, then we finally arrived home to find our power was out and our house was freezing 🥶 

Luckily my godmother put us up because the power outage lasted 4 days so we finally were just able to go home from our trip YESTERDAY! 🙈 At one point we just had to laugh because it was crazy how much stuff went wrong… but that’s life and that’s traveling sometimes 🌎 ✈️ 

The silver lining is we are home safe, Sadie is on the mend and we still managed to have a some fun in Mex 🇲🇽 

Curious, what’s the WORST TRIP you’ve ever been on and why? 👎🏼✈️

COMMUNITY ANNOUNCEMENT 📢 

Last week, co-founder Becky van Dijk announced she will be leaving We Are Travel Girls to pursue other entrepreneurial ventures. While we will miss her very much, she will always be part of We Are Travel Girls, and I'm humbled to have the opportunity to lead our community into the next chapter. ✈️

To echo Becky's sentiments, I'm incredibly proud of the community we've built together over the past seven years thanks to your support. We created We Are Travel Girls with the simple mission to promote and elevate the voices of female travelers. Since launch, we have published travel stories and guides from hundreds of female travel writers around the globe on WeAreTravelGirls.com that have helped empower women to travel the world with confidence. 🌎 

We also dreamed of bringing together travel-loving women in person as well as online. So I'm excited to announce that as the new CEO, I'm going to be focusing my energy on re-launching @TravelGirlsGetaways and hosting more in-person WATG Events in Los Angeles (where I live) and other cities around the world.

I'm passionate about giving back, so I'm also committed to using our platform to support and raise money for charity. We've supported charities through Travel Girls Giving in the past, and I'm excited to re-invigorate our charitable efforts with our impact trips, community fundraising, and our Charities We Love features. ❤️

At its core, We Are Travel Girls is about community, so I will also be re-launching our Ambassador Program, bringing on a handful of new ambassadors to write for us and co-host our events and trips. ✈️

If you're interested in becoming an ambassador, have a charity you'd like us to support, want us to consider your city for our next event, or if you have suggestions or questions please email me: vanessa@wearetravelgirls.com.

This is our community, I'm so grateful to be part of it, and I can't wait to see where we can take We Are Travel Girls in the coming years - together. ✨

X, @VanessaRivers

Would you live on a yacht? 🛥️

I lived on a yacht in Italy for 2 weeks in my twenties and it was magical ✨🇮🇹🙌🏼

I’m half Italian - my Grandma was from Palo del Colle (just outside of Bari) and my Grandpa was from Sicily 🇮🇹 They immigrated to New York when they were in their twenties and then had my father and his brother in NYC and so began our family’s new American roots 🇺🇸 

But Italy has always felt like a second home to me and I still have distant family that live in Palo del Colle 🇮🇹🍝🍷❤️

When I was in my twenties my father’s wealthy friend George Garvin Brown III (his family owned Brown Forman Distillery - Jack Daniels, Woodford Reserve etc 🥃) wanted to explore the Italian Coastline on his yacht and generously invited me and my father to join. We started in Bari and sailed down around Sicily and explored the beautiful Aeolian Islands 🏝️🇮🇹🥰

We didn’t know it at the time but this was to be Garvin’s last yacht trip. 🛥️ He was dying from cancer and hid from us because he wanted to have a carefree trip with friends 💔😭

Garvin was an incredibly kind, generous man and sparked my immense love of being at sea ❤️🌊 I sat on the bow of his boat for hours feeling like a queen, writing in my journal and gazing at the gorgeous coastline as the sea breeze wiped through my hair and the sun warmed my shoulders ☀️🛥️ 

It was a magical trip that I will cherish always. When it was time to say goodbye I cried like I baby because I loved every moment so much and knew I might never have the chance to live on a yacht again. 🛥️😭

If I’d known it would be Garvin’s last sail it would have been too heartbreaking to bare 💔 But I’ll always remember the good times we had on his boat and his incredible young, fun spirit that he kept till the very end of his life ☺️🙏🏼

Would you live on a yacht and what’s the longest time you’ve spent on a yacht? 🛥️ LMK in the comments👇🏼

#WeAreTravelGirls #Yacht #YachtLife

Have you been to Santa Barbara? ☀️🌊⚓️

Santa Barbara or “SB”, as the locals call it, is a picturesque beach town on the Central Coast of California nestled between the Santa Ynez Mountains and the sparkling pacific ocean. 🇺🇸

Downtown Santa Barbara offers Mediterranean-style white stucco buildings with red-tile roofs that reflect the city’s Spanish colonial heritage. 💛

I went to UCSB and lived in Santa Barbara for 10+ years and after traveling the world it’s still by far my favorite town! 🫶🏻 I live in Malibu currently so it’s a quick 1hr 15 min drive up the coast to SB so I sneak away there every chance I get! 🥰

Top things to do in SB include:
1) Sail with the SB Sailing Center @sbsailing 
2) Hike Inspiration Point & Cold Spring Trail 
3) Explore State Street & The Funk Zone 
4) Interact with sea life at the SB Sea Center 
5) Indulge at the candy & ice cream shops on Stearns Wharf
6) Enjoy wine with a view at Deep Sea Winery @deepseawine 

These are just a few of the many, MANY things to do in SB! Head over to WeAreTravelGirls.com (link in profile) to explore all our Santa Barbara Guides 🌎✈️

#WeAreTravelGirls #SantaBarbara #VisitSantaBarbara

It’s always summer somewhere… ☀️🌊

Save this post for your next trip to Mexico ✔️🇲🇽

If you’re looking for somewhere warm to escape to in the winter, Cabo is an excellent choice. The average temperature Nov - Jan is 82 degrees (28 Celsius) ☀️ and the average water temp is 75 degrees (24 Celsius) 💦🥰

Everyone stays in Cabo San Lucas but if you’re looking for a more authentic, affordable experience (just a 25 min drive from downtown Cabo) try staying in San José del Cabo 🇲🇽

After our girls getaway, I booked an affordable Airbnb in the Las Olas Condo complex on Costa Azul Beach (link in profile & stories) and stayed there solo for two days and did nothing but surf, relax, swim, read, go on beach walks and eat way too many fish tacos 🌊 🏄‍♀️🌮📚

I’ve stayed in this same complex dozens of times so I felt very safe being on my own and had a wonderful time! 🥰🇲🇽 

There’s a surf break and a surf shop in front, a small market around the corner and a good Mex restaurant next door plus it’s very close to SJD Airport ✈️ so it’s the perfect (AFFORDABLE) spot to stay solo or a great spot to stay with friends if you don’t want to deal with logistics 💛

Would you take a yacht out in the pouring rain? 🛥️🌧️😅

During our Cabo trip we reserved a boat for the day, and even though the weather was horrible, we decided to keep the reservation! 💦 Let’s just say, I would not recommend going out drinking the night before a boat day (rookie move) let alone the night before a stormy boat day. We honestly spent the first half of the day trying not barf 🤢 

But after a few hair of the dog margies 🍹 and a swim to the beach, we all started to feel much better and it was actually a cool experience being out at sea in the rain 🌊🌧️🙏🏼

Obviously, this wasn’t an ideal scenario having the one day we picked to rent a boat be totally stormy, but we made the best of it and it ended up being fun! 🤩 

Are you a “go with the flow” kind of traveler or do you need to have things “your way” in order to enjoy the trip? ✈️ 

I’m a chill person and always try to go with the flow on group trips and in life in general. 🙃 This group of girls I was with in Cabo all had a go with the flow mentality so we ended up having the absolute best time, even in the pouring rain and wind, hungover, on a boat 🛥️🌧️🇲🇽😅

Just sharing this little story to encourage you to try to go with the flow on your next trip. Even if things don’t work out how you planned, you’ll have A LOT more fun if you do 🤩✈️

#WeAreTravelGirls #GirlsGetaway #Cabo #ImOnABoat

Is it time for Thanksgiving yet? 🍁🦃🥰

Growing up Thanksgiving was always my favorite holiday. My mom, Christi, would cook this big, amazing meal and her and my stepdad, Todd, would let us invite anyone to join us who was going to be alone on the holiday. 🧡

My mom also made these beautiful fall flower arrangements with hallowed out pumpkins as the base / vase that she stuck everything into and tied up the bouquets with pretty burlap bows. 🍂Then she drove me and my brothers down to the local retirement home in Paso Robles (near where we grew up) and we passed out arrangements and visited with the elderly. 🥲 

My parents really made Thanksgiving about spending time with friends and family, giving thanks, being grateful, and giving back 🙏🏼 

I’m so grateful I got to experience Thanksgiving in that way growing up, and I hope I can create some of those experiences for my daughter, Sadie, who is 6 going on 16 - swipe to see [her sassy face] 😅🧡
